doc.previous: When working with digital audio digital signal processing techniques are commonly used to implement compression via digital audio editors or dedicated workstations Often the algorithms used emulate the above analog technologies
doc.after: A compressor reduces the level of an audio signal if its amplitude exceeds a certain threshold It is commonly set in decibels dB where a lower threshold e g 60 dB means a larger portion of the signal will be treated compared to a higher threshold of e g 5 dB
